@page "/priority"
 
<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Priority (Eager) Loading</h1>
    <p class="mb-8">
        The `Priority` tells BlazorImage to eagerly load this image, making it a high priority.<br/>
        This is
        useful for above-the-fold images that are visible immediately when the page loads, like hero images or product
        images on a product page.
    </p>

    <div class="border max-w-5xl p-4 mx-auto ">
        <Image Src="/images/photo.jpeg"
               Alt="Priority loaded image"
               Width="1200"
               Height="600"
               Priority="true" 
               Caption="Priority (Eager) Loading"
               EnableDeveloperMode="true" />

      
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <p class="font-medium">When to use priority:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2">
            <li>For the largest image visible within the viewport when the page loads</li>
            <li>For any image that is critical to the user experience</li>
            <li>For images that are above-the-fold</li>
            <li>Typically only needed for 1-3 images per page</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Code Example</h2>
        <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-md overflow-x-auto">

<code>
@("<")Image Src="/hero-image.jpg"
        Alt="Hero image"
        Width=1200
        Height=600
        Priority="true" // Priority is false by default
@("/>")
</code>
        </pre>
    </div>
</div>
